gomodel:SYNGO_4889  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Podocalyxin (PODXL) is a transmembrane protein originally detected in kidney podocytes. The present study shows its appearance at presynaptic terminals opposing dendritic spines in the hippocampus by immunogold localization (Fig. 5).. Experimental description: Post-embedding immunocytochemistry: OF1 adult mice (n= 2) were perfused... (p. 13)" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
